<br>
- &quot;They must test any changes that affect their area as they are implemented on <br>
Pendragon&quot;<br>
<br>
This is currently happening?  I doubt it is.  Perhaps it is independently of the TL, but not with and because of the TL unless I'm very much mistaken.<br>
<br>
-  &quot;maintaining contact with the player base beyond that as they see fit&quot;<br>
<br>
The last part leaves room for interpretation, but we have had no communication with our TL for quite some time now and not a wit throughout 1.62 which contains radical changes to the class.<br>
<br>
-  &quot;Their secondary role is to act as a class advocate&quot;<br>
<br>
Again, I see no evidence of this currently.  If I'm mistaken and you can show where our TL has taken up the proposed changes to Left Axe, then by all means do so.  We want an active TL and I'd love to learn that all we have is an issue of poor communication.<br>
<br>
Look, I'm not faulting anyone for withdrawing from the game to manage real life priorities.  Its perfectly understandable.  To do so for an extended period of time however - especially when radical changes are being made to the class you represent - is not right.  At the very least, name a temporary TL to act on your behalf or enlist the assistance of Garock who, to my knowledge, remains the Berserker TL Emeritus. <p>Jund Bloodaxe - 50th RR 5.7 Berserker - Palo<br>
Hammer Tyme - 50th RR 3.2 Skald - Palo<br>
Syf Stormcrow - 50th RR 3.5 Huntress - Palo<br>
